com.pump.util

Class PartitionIterator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.util.PartitionIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<java.util.List<java.util.List<T>>>

    public class PartitionIterator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<java.util.List<java.util.List<T>>>
    This breaks a list up into a series of partitions. For example, if you pass in the elements [A, B, C] with a partition count of 2, then this will return the lists: [], [A, B, C] [A], [B, C] [A, B], [C] [A, B, C], [] You can also define a minimum partition size. For example: if this is 1, then the example above will only include: [A], [B, C] [A, B], [C] The minimum partition size is enforced in the isValid(List) method, which subclasses can further modify if necessary to filter out combinations.
